us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame.interfaces

Interface FramePose3DBasics

  • All Superinterfaces:
    us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Clearable, FixedFramePose3DBasics, FrameChangeable, FramePose3DReadOnly, Pose3DBasics, Pose3DReadOnly, ReferenceFrameHolder, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Transformable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FramePose3D

    public interface FramePose3DBasics
extends FixedFramePose3DBasics, FrameChangeable
    Write and read interface for a 3D pose expressed in a changeable reference frame, i.e. the reference frame in which this pose is expressed can be changed.

    In addition to representing a Pose3DBasics, a ReferenceFrame is associated to a FramePose3DBasics. This allows, for instance, to enforce, at runtime, that operations on poses occur in the same coordinate system.

    Because a FramePose3DBasics extends Pose3DBasics, it is compatible with methods only requiring Pose3DBasics. However, these methods do NOT assert that the operation occur in the proper coordinate system. Use this feature carefully and always prefer using methods requiring FramePose3DBasics.
